==English==
{{see|ai|AI}}

===Etymology===
From [[Hebrew]] ''העי'' (''ai'', heap of ruins).

===Proper noun===
# (''[[Bible]]'') a [[Canaanite]] royal city mentioned in the [[Joshua|Book of Joshua]], popularly believed to be the modern archeoligical site [[Et-Tell]].
# (''[[Bible]]'') a city mentioned in [[Jeremiah]] 49:3 of unknown location, possibly the same city as definition 1.

